data.content:
Từ điển Anh - Việt
◘[,ouvə'rɔ:t]
*tính từ
 ■phải làm việc quá nhiều; mệt rã rời (vì làm việc quá nhiều)
 ■căng thẳng, bối rối
 ■gọt giũa quá kỹ càng, cầu kỳ

Anh - Anh
overwrought
■ adjective
1》 in a state of nervous excitement or anxiety.
2》 (of a piece of writing or a work of art) too elaborate or complicated in design or construction.
Origin
ME: archaic past participle of overwork.

Từ điển Đồng nghĩa
overwrought
▸ adjective
1she was too overwrought to listen: TENSE, agitated, nervous, on edge, edgy, keyed up, worked up, highly strung, neurotic, overexcited, beside oneself, distracted, distraught, frantic, hysterical; informal in a state, in a tizzy, uptight, wound up, het up; Brit.informal strung up.
2the painting is overwrought: OVER-ELABORATE, over-ornate, overblown, overdone, contrived, overworked, strained.
Opposites
calm, understated.

sentences.en: She was in very overwrought state after the accident.
sentences.vi: Cô ta ở trong trạng thái kích động mạnh sau vụ tai nạn.

sentences.en: Overwrought nerves brought sharpness to her voice and her hands clenched at her sides.
sentences.vi: Thần kinh quá căng thẳng khiến giọng nàng đâm gắt gỏng, hai tay nàng ghì chặt hai mạng sườn.

sentences.en: At the mention of Ashley's name, Scarlett's overwrought nerves gave way and she burst into tears.
sentences.vi: Nghe nhắc đến tên ashley, thần kinh quá căng thẳng của scarlett hết chịu nổi, nàng òa lên khóc.
